-- Mortgage Rate for 30-Year Loan Declines to Record 4.27%, Freddie Mac Says
-- B y   B i l l   K o e n i g
-- 2010-10-07T14:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/mortgage-rate-for-30-year-loan-declines-to-record-4-27-freddie-mac-says.html
The average rate on a 30-year home
loan fell to 4.27 percent for the week ending today, from 4.32
percent a week earlier, Freddie Mac, the McLean, Virginia-based
mortgage buyer, said today in an e-mailed statement. The 15-year
rate was 3.72 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bill Koenig at 
 wkoenig@bloomberg.net  